{
  "program": {
    "name": "GMES & Africa Programme",
    "one_liner": "The GMES & Africa initiative — a partnership between the African Union Commission (AUC) and the European Commission — has, since its launch in 2017, built a pan-African Earth-Observation (EO) infrastructure and capacity across the continent, enabling African institutions to access and use satellite and in-situ data for sustainable development, natural-resource management, water security, coastal/marine monitoring, climate resilience and disaster risk reduction. Phase 1 (2017–2021) with a budget of about €30 million mobilized 12 consortia involving over 120 institutions across 51 countries, deployed 12 e-stations, delivered geospatial services and trained thousands of African specialists. Phase 2 (2022–2025) leverages a €24.65 million grant to support 8 new consortia delivering African-driven EO services tailored to regional and national needs, promoting inclusion, capacity building, and embedding EO-based information into policy and decision-making for environment, natural resources, and climate adaptation. "
  },
